CRM (Customer Relationship Management) is a system or technology that helps businesses manage their interactions and relationships with customers.

It stores important customer information such as:

contact details,
purchase history,
conversations,
customer complaints,
and sales activities in one place.

The main goal of CRM is to help companies provide better customer service, improve communication, and increase sales.

For example, if a customer contacts a company again after purchasing a product, the employee can quickly view the customer’s previous orders and conversations through the CRM system. This helps the company respond faster and more personally.
Popular CRM platforms include
Salesforce
HubSpot
Zoho CRM


In simple terms, a CRM helps businesses keep customers happy and organized by managing all customer-related information efficiently.
